        <title>Participation in governance process during the election and post electoral periods in Burundi</title>
        <description>This project intends to implement five activities:
- Observation of election process in Burundi
- Preparation of modules and tools of awareness about the principles of good governance and about  the role of elected  representatives 
- Awareness of the new elected officials and representatives (450 in total) for their involvement in the democratic process 
- Conduct advocacy activities based on monitoring field activities of the elected. 

The CDJP with the parish facilitators will follow the elected on how they involve themselves on local governance issues  and prepare their reports. 
The CEJP will do the same thing - in collaboration with civil society stakeholders - at the national level.</description>
